<TEXT>
prime minister jozsef antall said 
wednesday he plans to tell soviet president mikhail s gorbachev 
that the warsaw pact is out of step with the political times and as 
a military alliance should be dissolved by next year 
we intend to make it clear that the warsaw pact as a political 
organization reflecting confrontation in europe is outdated 
said antall only hours before departure for a key pact summit in 
moscow 
soviet foreign minister eduard shevardnadze said tuesday that the 
pact would undertake a transformation at the moscow meeting and 
urged nato to do the same 
it has lost its function in europe antall said of the pact 
therefore its military aspect can be discarded and in our view 
dissolved by the end of 1991 
expanding on his proposal to transform the sevennation 
sovietled alliance into a nonmilitary pact antall told reporters 
it is to be attained through the helsinki process and the 
vienna disarmament talks 
the 35nation helsinki talks bring together all european nations 
except albania as well as the united states and canada to discuss 
various aspects of security and cooperation in europe the 16member 
north atlantic treaty organization and the warsaw pact are meeting 
in vienna to discuss cutting conventional arms in europe 
antall hungarys first noncommunist prime minister in more than 
four decades served notice shortly after assuming office last month 
that he sought to pull his country out of the pact he reiterated 
wednesday however that hungary would only leave with the agreement 
of all its pact partners 
the intentions of the hungarian people were made clear in 
1956 he said alluding to the nations failed attempt to leave the 
pact during the antistalinist revolution that was crushed by soviet 
tanks 
but that does not mean we can disregard international law 
politics and military aspects he said arguing against a renewed 
attempt on hungarys part to leave unilaterally 
antall also said he saw no reason for natos disbanding 
unlike the warsaw pact nato is not in crisis he said 
therefore the dissolution of the nato military alliance is not 
linked to the question of the future of the warsaw pact 
antall indicated hungary would seek more independence within the 
military alliance as long as it remained a member 
we want to compile as soon as possible a list of all the things 
we feel impinge upon the sovereignty of member states he said 
such stipulations and confrontational elements must be struck from 
the treaty 
