<TEXT>
the government has issued a package 
of antismoking measures in an attempt to discourage a habit shared 
by about a third of the countrys 150 million citizens 
the measures which went into effect at the beginning of june 
include a ban on cigarette sales to those under 18 a ban on tv 
advertising for cigarettes between 6 am and 9 pm and a ban on 
free samples 
they also include a recommendation to airline companies that 
smoking be outlawed on flights of less than two hours and a rule 
that the warning smoking is prejudicial to your health take up 
20 percent of the space on print ads and billboards for cigarettes 
current laws prohibiting smoking in elevators buses and other 
public areas are routinely ignored in brazil where an estimated 
546 million people smoke 
</TEXT>
