<TEXT>
the campaign for perus presidential runoff 
sunday is passionate and angry but polltakers say voters energies 
are devoted more toward defeating the candidate they dislike than 
electing someone they support 
many peruvians are uneasy with both mario vargas llosa perus 
celebrated novelist and his opponent alberto fujimori 
pollsters say each candidate inspires millions with emotions of 
disappointment and distrust 
at least half of fujimoris supporters are people who are 
scared of vargas llosa said alfredo torres of the polling firm 
apoyo of those who support vargas llosa at least a third are 
voting against fujimori 
polls show fujimori with a slim but firm lead over vargas llosa 
a novelistturnedpolitician who champions the free market most 
polls show fujimori the son of japanese immigrant parents with a 
5point lead nationally 
vargas llosa may have cut into that lead after his performance 
sunday night in a nationally broadcast debate with fujimori an 
apoyo poll of 1080 television viewers in lima and six other cities 
showed vargas llosa winning 48 to 37 percent 
the heated 2hour debate was marked by personal attacks 
fujimori accused vargas llosa of spreading insults and 
calumnies against him the novelist said his opponent offered only 
generalities and banalities in his campaign 
an agricultural engineer and former university rector with no 
political experience fujimori was the surprise of firstround 
elections april 8 he surged past seven opponents to nearly tie 
vargas llosa 
vargas llosa received 276 percent of the vote to fujimoris 246 
percent a runoff was required because no candidate received a 
majority 
vargas llosa has detailed plans for resolving perus worst 
economic crisis of the century and for battling a savage leftist 
insurgency 
like vargas llosa fujimori favors getting back on good terms 
with the international financial community by renewing payments on 
perus 19 billion foreign debt 
vargas llosa and fujimori both advocate economic development 
rather than police action to wean peasants away from perus 
billiondollar cocaine trade 
unlike the novelist fujimori has avoided discussing in detail 
his plans to reverse perus slide into economic chaos and civil war 
vargas llosa favors privatization of perus stateowned 
companies elimination of price controls and import barriers and an 
economic shock program to combat inflation 
fujimori opposes all three and thereby scores points with workers 
who fear for their jobs and with businesses that defend protective 
trade laws 
