limas provargas llosa television stations in little more than a 
month the novelist turned a 13point deficit into a 5point lead 
among voters in this city of 7 million 
but for vargas llosa the televised offensive has limits because 
fewer than half of perus 22 million people have access to 
television 
the antivargas llosa sentiment is especially strong in limas 
sprawling shantytowns and the impoverished countryside 
in the brutal campaign for the firstround elections garcias 
aprista party painted the novelist as the candidate of the rich 
white elite 
the effort was largely successful according to pollsters 
vargas llosas harsh antileft rhetoric also frightened away 
potential supporters among perus traditionally leftleaning 
electorate 
the result is a voting population deeply split along class lines 
most of vargas llosas gain has been among limas upper and 
middle classes the poor remain solidly opposed to him apparently 
unimpressed by the novelists recent campaign sweeps through their 
dusty shantytowns 
