china announced today it had freed 97 more 
participants in last years democracy movement after the anniversary 
of the movements bloody demise passed with only a few small 
protests 
the releases bring to 881 the number freed in the past six 
months out of thousands arrested but new arrests have been 
reported as recently as last week 
for the first time two top student leaders were among those 
freed xiong wei and zhou fengsuo both students at qinghua 
university were on the governments list of 21 mostwanted students 
and were arrested last june 
zhou was turned in by his sister and xiong surrendered in his 
mothers company according to official accounts 
