address broadcast late tuesday that authorities were trying to 
resolve the land dispute tass said 
housing is critically short in soviet central asia among the 
poorest regions of the nation 
lukyanov said the violence was triggered by a dispute over the 
ownership of 79 acres of uncultivated land 
but baktiyor hamidov head of the economic department of 
uzbekistans mission in moscow said in an interview that there is 
much more land at issue he said 618000 acres of cotton fields near 
the border is being made available by the uzbek government and local 
kirghiz authorities are controlling it 
they began dividing it between the families of mostly kirghiz 
descent he said and the uzbeks demanded it be divided evenly 
hamidov said the region was among the nations most densely 
populated with 500 to 1125 people per square mile he said 
disputes over land date back to 1924 when traditional boundaries 
were blurred by stalin 
leaders of uzbek groups also demanded that an autonomous region 
be set up inside kirghizia but negotiations on this subject 
produced no results tass reported without elaboration about 
onethird of oshs residents are uzbek 
