proposals for revamping the economy to a public referendum will be 
seen by many to be a desperate gamble the soviet economy is in a 
shambles 
this has pushed most of his economic advisers into ever greater 
pessimism about the possibility of effectively reforming the 
socialist economy as distinct from simply abandoning it altogether 
in favor of a fullfledged market system 
gorbachevs effort to seek public endorsement via a referendum 
and his hyperbole about the economic reform he is promoting being as 
profound a matter as the consequences of the october revolution 
itself shows how fragile his own situation is 
it is almost certain that his new economic package will not do 
the trick all efforts at decentralizing the socialist economy 
have ultimately failed 
but if gorbachev goes in for polishstyle shock therapy 
he will almost certainly provoke mass upsurges from an industrial 
work force which in numerical terms is the largest in the world 
