documentary that claimed he was involved in an alleged scheme with 
the soviet kgb to oust jakes last november 
the public is going to be informed about the future course of 
the investigation the terse ctk report that focused on bilak said 
samel said the four summoned for interrogation were asked to help 
police to clarify their activities related to the 1968 invasion 
and possibly other criminal activities as well 
they could have refused the summons but willingly complied 
he said 
jakes bilak and lenart were all expelled from the party after 
the november revolution that brought president vaclav havel to power 
in this weeks election havels civic forum which helped lead 
the anticommunist revolt is expected to emerge as a strong force 
although not to win an outright majority 
in april this year czechoslovak prosecutors launched an 
investigation into the 1968 sovietled invasion the investigation 
was to clarify what prosecutors have termed all circumstances of 
this criminal offense against peace 
that offense carries a maximum sentence of 15 years in jail 
lubomir veleta deputy general prosecutor said april 7 the main 
aim of the investigation was to identify people responsible for 
inviting the soviet troops into czechoslovakia 
bilak has long been accused to be the official who requested that 
soviet troops intervene but he has denied the charges 
the czechoslovak government has officially requested that soviet 
authorities release all documents related to the invasion but the 
kremlin has refused 
the invasion of soviet troops into czechoslovakia in 1968 was 
not decided on the basis of this or that appeal of individuals if 
there ever was such a thing soviet foreign ministry spokesman 
vadim perfiliev was quoted in a czechoslovak paper on may 29 as 
saying 
after the 1968 invasion bilak rose under the leadership of 
fellow slovak gustav husak to be chief communist party ideologue 
