<TEXT>
the united states and its nato allies 
are considering the increased use of multinational military units as 
a way of making western troops more acceptable in a unified germany 
analysts say 
richard fieldhouse senior research associate at the natural 
resources defense council in washington described the push for 
forces with soldiers from many nations as an attempt to maintain 
some sort of nato forces within germany 
all of this comes out of the desire to present stationed forces 
in a way which is more palatable to germany and the soviet union 
said hans binnendijk director of studies at the international 
institute for strategic studies in london 
the idea of multinational forces got a boost last month when us 
defense secretary dick cheney and other defense chiefs of the north 
atlantic treaty organization called for an alliance study of their 
use they said in a final statement that they attached particular 
importance to the task 
multinational forces air sea or ground units carrying the 
flags of a variety of nations are nothing new to nato 
but the new attention reflects the alliances campaign to revamp 
its military strategy with the diminished threat from the sovietled 
warsaw pact 
moreover it must deal with the prospects of a unified germany 
west germany belongs to nato but its eastern neighbor is part of 
the crumbling warsaw pact 
president mikhail s gorbachev of the soviet union has opposed 
nato membership for a united germany he recently suggested it could 
remain in the western alliance but must withdraw from its integrated 
military structure france and spain both nato allies are outside 
the joint military command 
in the changing situation fieldhouse said it would be difficult 
for the united states to make a case for keeping a large contingent 
of troops in germany what role does the united states have as a 
nato nation in germany he asked 
binnendijk said west germans doesnt want to be different from 
their european neighbors stationed forces make them abnormal 
he said 
as a result fieldhouse predicted germans probably wont be 
interested in having 195000 americans stationed on their soil in a 
relatively short period of time 
the united states has an estimated 239000 soldiers in west 
germany and the soviet union has 380000 red army troops on east 
german soil 
washington and moscow have settled on a plan as part of arms 
control talks in vienna that would reduce their forces stationed in 
central europe to 195000 soldiers on each side the united states 
would maintain an additional 30000 troops in britain and southern 
europe 
fieldhouse also argued that the continued presence of nato troops 
in germany would enable its allies to keep some form of influence 
in german affairs 
this would be perhaps one answer to any german interest in 
building up a military he said some in europe worry about the 
resurgence of a militaristic germany in the strategic center of 
their continent 
us gen john galvin the supreme commander of alliance forces 
in europe said natos air and sea forces already are made up of 
units from various nations 
it is really only the ground forces that are somewhat lacking 
in multinationality he said in a recent interview 
galvin suggested it might be best to form multinational ground 
units at the corps level a corps is usually made up of three 
divisions of 15000 to 20000 soldiers each each division would be 
drawn from a different nation 
he said he was concerned a smaller unit would be inefficient 
there is a certain level at which multinationality begins not to 
work very well he said 
he said it was difficult for instance to have a multinational 
crew in an airplane partly because of differences in language and 
training its hard to change that in an aircraft where you need 
to be in constant communication making quick decisions he said 
in 1960 nato formed the ace mobile force which draws air and 
ground troops from belgium canada germany italy luxembourg the 
netherlands britain and the united states their mission is to 
respond rapidly in an emergency 
there are about 5000 soldiers in the land unit and two to four 
squadrons with about 20 or so planes in each squadron in the air 
force 
last year the nato composite force was created to react quickly 
to an attack in northern norway it is made up of troops from 
canada west germany norway and the united states 
</TEXT>
