democratic leader george mitchell said 
wednesday an anticrime bill curbing semiautomatic weapons could be 
scuttled unless senators put a time limit on debate this week 
this is the vote on the crime bill mitchell said as senators 
prepared for a vote thursday to limit debate to 30 hours 
sponsors of the bill have been saying that without the time 
limit debating more than 241 proposed amendments would mean 
openended delays and make it impossible to vote on the overall 
legislation 
the bill would bar the import or domestic manufacture of nine 
semiautomatic assault rifles pistols and shotguns 
it also would provide for the death penalty for 30 federal 
crimes allow courts to consider evidence gathered with faulty 
warrants in some cases and move to end decadelong delays in 
carrying out death sentences 
mitchell was asked what would happen if the senate on thursday 
balked at a time limit on debate thats it the maine senator 
said sharply he suggested that the senate would then move on to 
other business and not return to the measure 
the campaign against militarylooking semiautomatic weapons began 
in january 1989 after a deranged man with an ak47 rifle opened fire 
on a stockton calif school yard leaving five dead and 30 injured 
the national rifle association has been against the plan saying 
that the assault weapons that would be restricted differ only in 
appearance from ordinary semiautomatic hunting rifles with their 
traditional brown wood stocks it says the bill would be unfair to 
hunters gun collectors and target shooters 
after senators rebuffed the nra two weeks ago and refused to drop 
the curbs lawmakers introduced scores of amendments 
but the senate on tuesday voted 5437 in favor of invoking 
cloture or imposing a time limit six votes short of the 60 needed 
the senate shelved further action on the crime package until 
after the thursday vote 
sen trent lott rmiss said on the floor wednesday that he 
cant understand why the crime package is being put off he said 
lawmakers had introduced some very good amendments to this issue 
the american people feel very strongly that the scales have 
tipped too much in favor of the criminals and against the victims 
and against the rights of society lott said 
he said there was nobody who is trying to delay this issue just 
because of the guncontrol question 
lets dont invoke cloture on thursday lets deal with these 
important amendments lott said he said americans dont 
understand parliamentary maneuver that prohibits amendments that are 
very important to them and should be on it 
