many senators are unwilling to recognize that aids is not spread 
through casual contact or through food 
the disabilities act has been hailed as the most significant 
piece of civil rights legislation since the 1964 civil rights act 
which banned discrimination against racial minorities 
it would protect the estimated 43 million disabled americans from 
job discrimination it also would guarantee them access to 
businesses entertainment accommodations and professional services 
as well as to public and private transportation and telephone 
service 
