falls on the canadian side of the border tuesday afternoon as 
tourists and police unable to help him looked on 
he was wearing neither a helmet nor a lifejacket 
his paddle emerged from the mist at the base of the falls about 
10 minutes after his plunge the dented red kayak inscribed 
rapidman surfaced about an hour later a few hundred yards 
downstream 
a day after the stunt sharps body had yet to surface it 
could be down there for weeks said niagara parks police constable 
