the hotselling 2 live crew rap 
album as nasty as they wanna be was declared obscene wednesday 
by a federal judge who cited its graphic sexual lyrics 
us district judge jose gonzalez agreed with the broward county 
sheriffs department that the album violates community obscenity 
standards 
it is an appeal to dirty thoughts and the loins not to the 
intellect and the mind gonzalez wrote in his opinion which was 
read to a packed courtroom that included the rap groups members 
the miamibased group sued after deputies threatened shopkeepers 
with arrest if they continued selling the album 
the groups attorney bruce rogow said hed appeal the ruling 
but predicted album sales which are approaching 2 million would 
get a boost from the decision 
i think the demand for the record is going to be 
extraordinary rogow said quoting a newspaper columnist who 
wrote people will crawl naked over broken glass to get what 
someone tells them theyre not supposed to 
gonzalez said the recording met the 1973 us supreme court test 
for obscenity as set by local community standards and cited state 
laws in his ruling 
florida has declared obscenity a crime he wrote to 
repeat violation of the law against obscenity is as much against 
the law as assault rape kidnapping robbery or any other form of 
behavior which the legislature has declared criminal 
the judge who listened to the album at a hearing in midmay and 
heard arguments from witnesses and attorneys did rebuke the 
sheriffs office for improper prior restraint of free speech he 
said deputies shouldnt have approached retailers until the material 
had been declared obscene 
