<TEXT>
us immigration investigators say they expect 
manuel noriega to be charged with being at the center of the largest 
aliensmuggling ring ever uncovered 
tens of thousands of chinese cubans and other immigrants paid 
millions of dollars to panamanian officials to use that nation as an 
illegal gateway to the united states and canada said robert harris 
chief criminal investigator for the immigration and naturalization 
service here 
the ring started as early as 1980 and about 4000 cubans used it 
to enter this country at miami international airport alone during 
the past seven years authorities said sixteen thousand people were 
caught in the pipeline when the united states invaded panama in 
december said robert penland who recently retired as assistant ins 
commissioner for antismuggling 
nobody ever operated an aliensmuggling operation to the extent 
of panama harris said it was operated by the government and 
it was a wellorganized wellrun operation 
he said immigration officials could not recall any such 
stateoperated alien trade 
there is already enough evidence to seek indictments harris 
said but ins and federal prosecutors decided to move cautiously 
because of the former panamanian dictators protracted 
drugsmuggling case due to go to trial next year 
we dont want to interfere with the current prosecution effort 
by the united states attorney he said recently any indictment 
could be after the trial 
in response to harris comments us attorney dexter lehtinen 
issued a statement wednesday saying there is no indictment 
currently planned or contemplated against general manuel a noriega 
in this district that includes any allegations of alien smuggling 
the allegations became public during a january bond hearing for a 
noriega codefendant pilot eduardo pardo when federal prosecutors 
said noriega and pardo helped smuggle aliens into the country 
noriega attorney frank rubino said he was surprised by the 
investigation and questioned the us right to prosecute his client 
in such a case 
the united states may like to police the world but theyve 
just gone a step too far rubino said what may have occurred 
internally in the country of panama is not within us 
jurisdiction 
the smuggling operation not only involved noriega and top 
intelligence officials but also panamas consulates the cuban 
government private attorneys and usbased smugglers 
investigators say 
panamanian officials acting directly or through private attorney 
middlemen charged from 10000 up to 20000 for visas into panama 
harris said he said the highest prices were paid by refugees from 
china while those from cuba hong kong and other points paid 
somewhat less harris said 
cuban officials worked with noriega on the visas to extract money 
from refugees leaving that island for panama and miamibased cuban 
rights groups also paid noriega to ensure their countrymen were 
cleared to travel to the united states harris said 
trusted noriega inlaws were put in charge of two of the most 
lucrative consulates taiwan and hong kong said the investigator 
all visa approvals had to come directly from the head of panamas 
intelligence service lt col rafael cedeno or from noriega 
himself harris said cedeno distributed a list to panamanian 
customs officials and no one could enter the country unless they 
were on it harris said 
entering panama was only the beginning however harris said 
once they arrived they were further exploited they would sell 
them residence visas extensions of stay sometimes 3000 to stay 
an extra year 
maj felipe camargo who headed panamas immigration agency for 
only four months was captured after the us invasion and is one of 
several former top officials to give details on how lucrative the 
ring was said harris 
in that four months he admitted personally getting 300000 
said harris if he got 300000 the higherups must have gotten 
at least that amount 
all orders came directly from noriega and cedeno at the 
panamanian defense forces headquarters the comandancia 
and the money was then passed on to the comandancia said 
harris that would be noriega or cedeno or cedenos 
predecessor guillermo wong before the october coup attempt 
after the invasion the panamanians apparently tried to destroy 
all financial records but investigators found one set of wire 
transfers to cedeno for 80000 they believe are linked to the 
aliensmuggling 
even when the aliens made arrangments to sneak into the united 
states they still had to pay panamanian officials to get on 
cedenos exit list said harris 
smuggling into the united states from panama was accomplished in 
various forms said harris while cubans could simply show up in the 
united states and claim political asylum chinese aliens had more 
difficulty 
they take a different route they try to evade the ins through 
fraudulent documents or cross over land borders he said 
as far as the ins can tell the new government of panama has 
stopped the alien trade into the country officials said 
but about 7000 chinese were stranded in panama after the 
invasion so the smuggling operations out of that country continue 
even though no longer organized by the government immigration 
officials said the 8000 others were either in the home countries 
in third countries or were still making their way into the united 
states officials said 
a flight of illegal chinese immigrants from panama was recently 
intercepted in canada and harris said arrests are still being made 
in miami 
