he arrived wednesday on the first leg of a sixweek transatlantic 
trip aimed at persuading the west to maintain pressure on south 
africas white rulers 
mandela freed feb 11 after more than 27 years in prison was 
met at orly airport by frances first lady danielle mitterrand 
head of a human rights foundation that has lobbied against apartheid 
