the bush administration moved wednesday to 
defuse controversy over government financing of potentially 
objectional art by proposing a oneyear interim extension of the 
national endowment for the arts 
endowment director john e frohnmayer told a senate panel he 
hoped time would allow the temperature to go down on the dispute 
over federal aid of allegedly obscene art 
he urged that a 12member advisory commission half of it 
appointed by congress and half by the white house be given time to 
reach some recommendations about the future of the endowment and its 
grantmaking procedures 
this problem must be solved and i pledge to you my full 
