debilitating to my agency 
frohnmayer appeared before a senate appropriations subcommittee 
considering the budget for the nea the agencys legislative 
authorization is scheduled to expire at the end of this fiscal year 
president bush has recommended another fiveyear renewal or 
reauthorization of the nea with no restrictions on its grantmaking 
authority but the nea has drawn opposition among conservatives 
because of federal grants for controversial works by the late 
photographer robert mapplethorpe and photographer andrews serrano 
and congressional supporters have acknowledged it would be difficult 
to win full renewal with no restrictions 
frohnmayer told the panel that the bush administration continues 
to prefer a fiveyear reauthorization of the nea without 
restrictions but would accept a threeyear or even a oneyear 
extension while awaiting the commissions recommendation 
at the white house deputy press secretary alixe glen called a 
oneyear extension the prudent thing to do 
given the political climate this isnt something we want to do 
hastily she said 
the advisory commission met separately wednesday for the first 
time to review the agencys grantmaking procedures its first 
meeting came more than a month after it had been directed by 
congress to make a report on the nea frohnmayer cited 
administrative delays and urged that the commissions life also be 
extended beyond its october expiration 
