barrel but they surely will byrd said 
mcclure said he wanted to continue supporting the arts but 
complained of an attitude out there among the arts community 
that congress has no business exercising control on grants 
frohnmayer acknowledged the controversy has damaged the nea and 
said the endowment has taken steps to ensure grants go through 
careful review 
