<TEXT>
the bush administration has informed congress 
it intends to sell saudi arabia more than 4 billion worth of light 
armored vehicles tow antitank missiles and modernization packages 
for five awacs surveillance planes the pentagon said wednesday 
if congress doesnt object within 30 days the sales are allowed 
to go through in the formal prenotice period during which the 
proposed arms sales were made known to members of congress no 
objections were raised by lawmakers 
the sales help fulfill saudi arabias defense needs and support 
us strategic interests in the region the pentagon said 
the sales also help boost us weapons producers many of whom 
face the prospect of sharp reductions in us defense spending 
for the most part the saudis military arsenal is usmade 
though the desert kingdom concluded a 30 billion multiyear deal 
with british companies several years ago for fighter planes and 
other weapons 
this sale will contribute to the foreign policy and national 
security of the united states by helping improve the security of a 
friendly country which has been and continues to be an important 
force for political stability and economic progress in the middle 
east the pentagon said 
the largest of three separate packages announced by the defense 
department carries a 34 billion price tag and is destined to 
support the saudi national guard the pentagon said 
that package includes 1117 light armored vehicles 2000 tow 11a 
antitank missiles 116 tow missile launchers 27 m198 155mm 
howitzers ammunition support equipment the design and 
construction of ranges and maintenance facilities for the equipment 
and us government and contractor managment training logistical 
and technical support for the items the statement said 
the lav is a multipurpose vehicles that carries a 25mm automatic 
cannon and a machine gun it is used by the us marines primarily 
as a reconnaisance vehicle as a troop carrier or as a 
lightarmored command and control center 
the other two packages include 
a 600 million modification and system integration program 
for five awacs airborne warning and control system surveillance 
aircraft and eight ke3 tanker aircraft to improve their mission 
navigation engine and aircraft protection systems the pentagon 
said 
the pentagon said the systems were necessary for a common 
configuration with similar us aircraft and to provide saudi 
arabia with an effective air defense command and control network 
capable of countering all potential threats in the persian gulf 
region 
the awacs were the subject of a bruising battle in congress in 
1981 over the introduction of such sophisticated aircraft into the 
volatile mideast region 
a 26 million sale of 12 m88a1 recovery vehicles with 
additional weapons and equipment including 12 m2 50caliber 
machine guns spare and repair parts 
the sale augments and earlier sale of nine such vehicles which 
are heavily armored and designed to tow damaged tanks or other 
tracked vehicles from the battlefield 
the prime contractor for the awacs and tanker equipment sale is 
boeing aircraft co of seattle 
the prime contractor for the lav sale is general motors of 
canada for teh tow missiles the prime contractor is hughes 
aircraft corp of tombstone ariz 
the prime contractor for the recovery vehicles is bowen 
mclaughlin york corp of york pa 
