injuries was lobbed into the embassy compound by an unknown 
assailant an administration official said 
the embassy complex the largest in subsaharan africa boasts 
three swimming pools and a ninehole golf course 
the official speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
seaside capital has been beset in recent months by fuel shortages 
water and electricity interruptions and rampant crime the 
security situation is at a nadir he said 
foreign reporters are usually denied access to somalia at the 
tip of the horn of africa on the eastern approaches to the red sea 
and reliable information about the situation there is hard to obtain 
