vladimir zhironovsky chairman of the liberal 
democrats conducts interviews on a park bench not in an office 
his party couldnt afford an office even if one were available 
we dont have any money we dont have any press we dont have 
any advertising he said on the bench in a quiet shady corner of 
sokolniki park in northeast moscow 
nikolai travkin a plainspoken former communist party member who 
is forming a populist movement incites disgruntled citizens to 
throw out his former comrades the russian social democrats are 
looking for coalition partners and communists need not apply 
dozens of parties have formed since the communists and the 
national legislature agreed in february to end the partys monopoly 
on power the political spectrum ranges from monarchist to 
anarchist but the communist party remains dominant 
communist reformer vyacheslav n shostakovsky said the newcomers 
