latemay sales of north americanmade vehicles 
dipped just 33 percent from last years strong pace but analysts 
say real demand is weaker than the figures show 
the 10 major us car and truckmaking companies tuesday 
reported they sold vehicles at an average of 51002 a day during may 
2131 compared with a rate of 52767 during the same time last year 
a 59 percent drop in car sales more than offset a 16 percent 
rise in sales of trucks spurred mainly by general motors corp 
minivan and ford motor cos explorer sportutility vehicle sales 
although the sales pace picked up sharply from midmays 
disaster level i would not label overall demand as strong said 
analyst tom webb with the national automobile dealers association in 
mclean va 
the latemay sales drop came against a strong period last year 
when incentives were luring consumers into showrooms automakers 
lately have been trying to wean car buyers from rebates and 
lowinterest financing 
the latest figures would have been worse if not for another surge 
in sales of transplants cars made in the united states at 
japaneseowned factories 
latemay sales of cars made in north america by gm ford and 
chrysler corp fell 107 percent while transplant sales rose 23 
percent 
