strength of the transplant sales figures was a statistical quirk 
for instance us sales arms of toyota motor corp and honda 
motor co ltd reported they sold as many cars in the last 10day 
selling period of the month as they did in the first two periods 
combined 
we have another endofthemonth dramatic recovery in cars 
sales that doesnt mean a thing healy said i think youve got 
to look at car sales in the last 30 days and if you do that its 
going to smooth out that endofthemonth bulge 
for all of may domestic producers reported a 78 percent decline 
in car and truck sales with imported vehicles included sales ran 7 
percent behind the may 1989 level 
the big threes share of the us car market stood at about 61 
percent last month down from 66 percent a year before the 
transplants share of the market was about 12 percent in may 
compared with 73 percent a year ago imports made up the balance 
the industry softness reinforces a report issued monday by the 
conference board saying consumer confidence slipped slightly last 
month 
so far for the year sales of domestic and imported vehicles were 
43 percent behind last years pace with sales of domestic cars and 
trucks down 39 percent and import sales off 56 percent 
