<TEXT>
britain introduced a smaller five pound note 
wednesday that includes a new engraving of a gracefully aging queen 
the change the first in two decades is designed to combat 
hightech forgeries and cut production costs the new note is 
scheduled to be released into circulation on thursday 
no item created by man cant be recreated said nigel 
bevittsmith manager of design and development at the bank of 
englands printing works what we try to do is to make it 
timeconsuming and as expensive as possible 
the fivepound notes have been reduced in size from 57by3 
inches to 53by27 inches 
among the other changes the dominant blue in the notes was 
lightened from navy to turquoise and a blend of background colors 
was created to challenge sophisticated forgers who use modern color 
reproduction machines 
also the position and color of the numbers was changed and a 
silvercolored windowed thread running through the note was added 
the bank of england which already has printed 200 million of the 
new notes said queen elizabeths new portrait shows the monarch 
gracefully aged rather than as a delicate brunette young enough 
to be prince charles sister 
railway pioneer george stephenson replaces the duke of wellington 
on the new notes 
all english notes will be redesigned over the next four years and 
will be between 16 percent and 22 percent smaller the bank of 
england said 
</TEXT>
