<TEXT>
shearson lehman hutton inc overhauled its 
operations wednesday reviving a respected investment banking name 
and dumping a vestige of its expansionist 1980s in a bid to rebound 
from record losses on wall street 
the restructuring marks another step by parent american express 
co to reverse the fortunes of the nations second largest 
brokerage which lost 915 million in the first three months of the 
year 
shearson said it was grouping into two divisions from four 
shearson lehman brothers for individual investing and asset 
management and lehman brothers for investment banking and capital 
markets activities the full firm will be known as shearson lehman 
brothers inc 
in the investment banking division shearson hopes resurrecting 
the 140yearold lehman brothers name will mean more respect and 
cache during one of the slowest periods in wall street history 
we hope the lehman brothers name will have the magic still 
shearson chairman and chief executive howard l clark jr said in an 
interview a little magic wouldnt hurt 
shearson acquired the lehman brothers kuhn loeb inc investment 
bank in 1984 as part of a rapid growth strategy during the 
dealheavy 80s dubbing the new firm shearson lehman brothers inc 
same as the new one 
lehman brothers dates to 1850 when it was founded by immigrants 
from bavaria as a commodities house in montgomery ala the 
investment bank was among those dominating wall street in the early 
1900s and grew rapidly after world war ii 
about 1000 lehman brothers veterans still work at shearson the 
no2 brokerage behind merrill lynch amp co 
under thenchairman peter cohen who was ousted earlier this year 
by american express chairman james d robinson iii shearson 
acquired ef hutton amp co shortly after the 1987 stock market crash 
by dropping hutton from its name shearson erases the public 
connection with a merger that fostered a clash of corporate cultures 
and has been called the firms biggest expansion mistake 
clark said the new structure organizes the firm along customer 
lines with shearson lehman brothers for individual investments and 
lehman brothers for institutions he said the new shape would 
focus accountability and responsibility of the business to 
respond to client needs and interests 
clark is part of the american express invasion running the 
shearson overhaul when he was picked to head the firm he was chief 
financial officer of american express and his father is a former 
chairman of the company 
the credit card and travel service giant in recent months has put 
more than 1 billion in capital into shearson and is buying all of 
the brokerages remaining common stock american express now holds 
61 percent of shearson 
shearson lost an industry record 915 million in the first 
quarter in part because of expenses to pay for a restructuring 
including about 2000 layoffs most wall street firms have been 
forced to cut back because of an industry slowdown since the stock 
market crash shearson also has been criticized for bad management 
overexpansion and excessive spending during the last decade 
shearson said its boston co money management subsidiary would 
remain a separate business 
richard s fuld jr a lehman veteran and current president of 
shearsons capital markets group and sherman r lewis jr 
president of investment and merchant banking were named cochief 
executives of the new lehman brothers division 
that division will serve corporations governments and 
institutions including capital markets sales research and trading 
as well as investment and merchant banking 
as expected jonathan s linen an american express executive 
was named president and chief executive of the shearson lehman 
brothers division linen currently is president and chief executive 
of american express direct marketing and travelers checks group 
