aluminum company of america after 91 years of operation the company 
said wednesday 
the mines located near little rock ark are adjacent to 
alcoas arkansas operations which includes a bauxite refinery and 
chemical facilities for processing alumina an oxide of aluminum 
present in bauxite 
some of the employees retired and others were laid off when the 
mines closed last week the refining operations also are being shut 
down alcoa said 
the mining and refining operations were ended because the 
reserves of bauxite were no longer economical to mine and refine 
the company said 
the bauxite was used to make about 275000 metric tons of alumina 
a year 
alumina once was used in the production of aluminum but recently 
was used mostly to produce chemicals for cements ceramics fire 
retardants paper and pharmaceuticals the company said 
about 700 employees who will remain at the plant will make 
chemicals from alumina feedstocks from other alcoa locations the 
company said 
the worlds largest reserves of bauxite are in australia brazil 
guinea jamaica suriname and venezuela 
