support two of us he said but if greyhound fails cascade is 
ready to run buses to every town greyhound serves in washington he 
said 
while greyhound is the only bus system operating nationwide 
about 200 smaller lines run limited routes most of the other 1800 
lines carry tours and charters overall its a 12 billion industry 
charter lines that can charge more now that greyhound has scaled 
back its lowpriced charter services also are benefiting from the 
strike said industry officials 
but some bus companies say they are hurting because greyhound 
does their ticketing and hasnt been turning over the revenue and 
because the image of bus travel in general has been sullied by 
violence during the greyhound strike 
