surrender shortterm profits from thwarted takeover bids 
first city said the takeover law and the largely unsuccessful 
proxy fight played a role in the decision 
the agreement calls for first city to pay armstrong 605000 and 
for armstrong to pay first city affiliates 5 million 
the payments are in part reimbursement of first citys expenses 
related to the proxy fight scheldrup said 
in addition the belzbergs have agreed not to pursue their 
petition proposing changes in armstrongs articles of incorporation 
the states antitakeover legislation was drafted last year after 
the belzbergs first disclosed an interest in acquiring the company 
in addition to garnishing raiders profits the law also restricts 
the voting rights of raiders and preserves labor contracts when 
corporations exchange hands 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

