<DOCNO> AP900606-0296 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
metromedia co was awarded 46 million in damages 
wednesday in its civil racketeering lawsuit against william fugazy 
an operator of travel agencies and limousine services 
the lawsuit was over metromedias 1985 purchase of fugazy express 
inc car service which is now in bankruptcy proceedings 
a sixmember jury in us district court found that fugazy had 
misrepresented to metromedia the companys financial condition and 
certain liabilities 
the jury awarded 156 million in damages which under civil 
racketeering statute is trebled to more than 46 million 
anthony princi fugazys attorney said he would appeal 
the lawsuit also named fugazys son roy and two of fugazys 
companies but the jury rejected all charges against them 
the trial lasted three weeks and included testimony from fugazy 
and billionaire john kluge who controls metromedia 
metromedia is a privately held partnership that owns companies in 
the telecommunications software restaurant and hotel industries 
it previously sold its television stations to the fox network 
the fugazy family owns a chain of travel agencies and a separate 
limousine service in new york 
metromedia attorney martin shelton said fugazy had overstated the 
value of fugazy express by 7 million to 8 million and had given 
metromedia inaccurate earnings figures 
shelton also said that metromedia had invested about 30 million 
in fugazy express 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

